Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{a drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{18-20%mins}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with 1/4 tsp @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a sieve.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g} and @vegan 'Nduja{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Cook until fragrant, ~{1%min}.

Add the beans, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%mins}.

Once thickened, add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g}, roasted sweet potato and @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed, then remove from the heat. Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon over the sweet potato and beans.

Sprinkle on the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g} to finish.

Enjoy!